人類的起源在19世紀的西方引起了激烈的學術爭論，單地起源論支持者以《[[聖經|聖經]]》中亞當夏娃的故事為立論基礎，而多地起源論支持者則強調感知上的差異，因此受到[[白人至上主義|白人至上主義者]]，尤其是美國奴隸主的歡迎<ref>Ibram X. Kendi, Stamped from the Beginning. The Definitive History of Racist Ideas in America, New York: Nation Books 2016. {{ISBN|978-1-5685-8464-5}}, chapters 4, 7–12, 14, 16 ''passim''.</ref>。

英國生物學家湯瑪士·亨利·赫胥黎（Thomas Henry Huxley）是一個堅實的達爾文主義和單地起源論的提倡者，他在1865年提出了對多地起源論支持者的觀點：「某些人想像人種是在我們發現他們的地方被創造出來...而蒙古人種則源自[[紅毛猩猩|紅毛猩猩]]。」<ref name="HuxEssay">Huxley, Thomas. ''Collected Essays of Thomas Huxley: Man's Place in Nature and Other'' Kessinger Publishing: Montana, 2005. p.247. {{ISBN|1-4179-7462-1}}</ref>。

在19世紀，西方學術界為馬來人和美洲原住民是否應被歸類為蒙古人種發表了各式各樣的意見。例如，D. M. Warren在1856年根據蒙古人種的狹義定義而將馬來人和美洲原住民排除在外<ref>Warren, D.M. (1856). A System of Physical Geography. Philadelphia: H. Cowperthwait & Co. p. 77.</ref>，赫胥黎和亞歷山大·溫切爾（Alexander Winchell）則分別在1870年和1881年將馬來人和美洲原住民歸類為蒙古人種<ref>{{cite web |url=http://aleph0.clarku.edu/huxley/SM3/GeoDis.html |title=Huxley, Thomas, On the Geographical Distribution of the Chief Modifications of Mankind. 1870. August 14, 2006 |publisher=Aleph0.clarku.edu |access-date=2013-12-15 |archive-date=2010-12-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101212220953/http://aleph0.clarku.edu/huxley/SM3/GeoDis.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>Winchell, A. (1881). Preadamites; or A Demonstration of the Existence of Men Before Adam; (3rd ed.). Chicago: S.C. Griggs and Company; London: Trubner & Co. pp. 57, 66.</ref>。而在1861年，法國動物學家伊西多爾·若弗魯瓦·聖希萊爾（Isidore Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire）甚至將澳大利亞原住民列為蒙古人種的一個亞種<ref name="Deniker">Deniker, Joseph. ''The Races of Man: An Outline of Anthropology and Ethnography'' C. Scribner's Sons: New York, 1900, p.282 {{ISBN|0-8369-5932-9}}</ref>。

「蒙古人種」的定義最初與膚色無關，直到19世紀50年代，法國貴族[[阿蒂爾·德·戈比諾|阿蒂爾·德·戈比諾]]出版了一本名為《Essai sur l'inégalité des races humaines》的著作，才首次將人種以膚色分為三大類：白、黑、黃。在他定義下的「黃種人」包括所有在當時被其他學者歸類為蒙古人種的族群<ref name="Gob">{{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/inequalityhuman00gobigoog |year=1915 |publisher=Putnam |last=Gobineau |first=Arthur |title=The Inequality of Human Races |access-date=2007-10-18|page=146|isbn=978-0-86527-430-3}}</ref><ref name="anthroGob">DiPiero, Thomas. ''White Men Aren't'' gid/s work Duke University Press, 2002, p.8 {{ISBN|0-8223-2961-1}}</ref>。戈比諾的種族論述對[[希特勒|希特勒]]影響深遠。在戈比諾眼中，「白種人」地位超然，「黃種人」在體質和智力上皆平庸，但極端的物質主義傾向卻使他們也能有些微成就<ref name="#1">{{cite journal |last=Blue |first=Gregory |title=Gobineau on China: Race Theory, the "Yellow Peril" and the Critique of Modernity" |journal=[[Journal_of_World_History|Journal of World History]] |volume=10 |issue=1 |pages=93–139 | year=1999 |jstor=20078751 |doi=10.1353/jwh.2005.0003 |s2cid=143762514 }}</ref>。

而根據[[邁耶百科詞典|邁耶百科詞典]]（1885-1890年）的定義，蒙古人種則包括西伯利亞人、汉人、印度支那人、[[日本人|日本人]]、韓國人、藏人、緬甸人、馬來人、波利尼西亞人、毛利人、密克羅尼西亞人、愛斯基摩人和美洲原住民<ref>''[[Meyers_Konversations-Lexikon|Meyers Konversations-Lexikon]]'', 4th edition, 1885–90.</ref>。

=== 二十世纪 ===
1909年，一張基於赫伯特·霍普·瑞斯利（Herbert Hope Risley）的種族劃分構想的地圖被發表，並將[[孟加拉人|孟加拉人]]和奧里薩人列為蒙古-達羅毗荼人種，認為他們是蒙古人種和達羅毗荼人種的混血種族<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PwNkQgAACAAJ |title=The Concept of Race in South Asia |first=Peter |last=Robb |date=1997-04-21 |publisher=Oxford University Press |via=Google Books |isbn=978-0-19-564268-1 |access-date=2021-06-09 |archive-date=2016-05-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520210806/https://books.google.com/books?id=PwNkQgAACAAJ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在這之前5年，即1904年，[[龐南巴拉姆·阿魯納恰拉姆|龐南巴拉姆·阿魯納恰拉姆]]亦提出了類似構想，認為[[斯里蘭卡|斯里蘭卡]]的[[僧伽羅人|僧伽羅人]]是蒙古人種和馬來人種的混血種族<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://krex.k-state.edu/dspace/bitstream/handle/2097/32648/StefanSchubert2016.pdf?sequence=1 |title=存档副本 |access-date=2021-06-09 |archive-date=2021-07-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210716231505/https://krex.k-state.edu/dspace/bitstream/handle/2097/32648/StefanSchubert2016.pdf?sequence=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[納粹德國|納粹德國]]體質人類學家在埃貢·弗賴赫爾·馮·埃克斯坦德特（Egon Freiherr von Eickstedt）亦採用與瑞斯利和阿魯納恰拉姆相同的分類法將[[尼泊爾|尼泊爾]]、[[不丹|不丹]]、[[孟加拉|孟加拉]]、[[東印度|東印度]]、印度東北部部分地區、緬甸西部和斯里蘭卡的族群視作印度人和南蒙古人的混血種族<ref>{{cite journal |jstor=29535004 |title=Die Indien-Expedition des Staatlichen Forschungsinstituts für Völkerkunde in Leipzig. 1. Anthropologischer Bericht |first=Egon Frhr. |last=von Eickstedt |date=2018-04-21 |journal=Anthropologischer Anzeiger |volume=4 |issue=3 |pages=208–219}}</ref>。他同時亦將緬甸中部、雲南、西藏南部、泰國和印度部分地區的族群命名為德昂人種（以緬甸[[德昂族|德昂族]]命名）。在他的定義中，斯里蘭卡人、[[蒙達人|蒙達人]]、緬族、克倫族、克欽族、[[撣族|撣族]]、泰族、''嶺南華人''都是「混了血」的德昂人種<ref>{{cite web |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ykgRAQAAMAAJ |title=Rassenkunde und Rassengeschichte der Menschheit |first=Egon von |last=Eickstedt |date=2018-04-21 |publisher=F. Enke |via=Google Books |access-date=2021-06-09 |archive-date=2021-12-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221111335/https://books.google.com/books?id=ykgRAQAAMAAJ |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{需要引文}}。

[[聯合國教科文組織|聯合國教科文組織]]在1950年發表了一個名為《種族問題》的聲明，指有鑒於對種族主義中認為種族不平等的教義為[[第二次世界大戰|第二次世界大戰]]的成因之一<ref name="UNESCO1950">[http://unesdoc.unesco.org/images/0012/001282/128291eo.pdf "The Race Question"] {{Wayback|url=http://unesdoc.unesco.org/images/0012/001282/128291eo.pdf |date=20110208103512 }}, UNESCO, 1950, 11pp</ref>，提議以「民族」代替「種族」<ref name="UNESCO1950" />。

美國人類學家卡爾頓·庫恩（Carleton S. Coon）在1961年發表了他的極具爭議的著作《種族起源》 ，他將智人分為五種：高加索人種、蒙古人種、[[澳大利亞人種|澳大利亞人種]]、[[開普敦人種|開普敦人種]]和剛果人種<ref name="ways">{{cite journal| last = Jackson Jr.| first = John| title="In Ways Unacademical": The Reception of Carleton S. Coon's The Origin of Races| journal = Journal of the History of Biology| volume = 34| issue = 2| pages = 247–285|date=June 2001| doi = 10.1023/A:1010366015968 | jstor=4331661| s2cid = 86739986}}</ref>。庫恩的論點是，直立人本身就分為五種，然後又各自演化成智人<ref>Cited according to {{cite journal| last = Jackson Jr.| first = John| title="In Ways Unacademical": The Reception of Carleton S. Coon's The Origin of Races| journal = Journal of the History of Biology| volume = 34| issue = 2| page = 248|date=June 2001| doi = 10.1023/A:1010366015968 | jstor=4331661| s2cid = 86739986}} The reference given there is to "Coon, ''Origin of the'' [sic] ''Races'', 1963 [sic], p. 657".</ref>。但由於庫恩是依循傳統體質人類學依賴形態特徵的判斷法而非以新興的遺傳學來區分人種，因此他的《種族起源》被視為快被取代的過時科學方法的苟延殘喘<ref name="ways" />{{rp|249}}<ref>For a criticism of Coon's relying on typology alone, see also: {{cite web |url=https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/first/gill.html |title=Does Race Exist? A proponent's perspective |first=George W. |last=Gill |publisher=Pbs.org |year=2000 |access-date=2021-06-09 |archive-date=2021-11-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211104173713/https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/first/gill.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 現代遺傳學 ===
西方學者認為隨著現代遺傳學發展，舊有的種族概念在生物學範疇已變得站不住腳<ref>{{cite web |author1=Vivian Chou |title=How Science and Genetics are Reshaping the Race Debate of the 21st Century |url=http://sitn.hms.harvard.edu/flash/2017/science-genetics-reshaping-race-debate-21st-century/ |publisher=Harvard University |access-date=2021-06-15 |archive-date=2020-12-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201214152451/http://sitn.hms.harvard.edu/flash/2017/science-genetics-reshaping-race-debate-21st-century/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，這些分類對遺傳學研究一點用處也沒有<ref name="#2">{{cite journal |author1=Lieberman, L. |title=Race" 1997 and 2001: A Race Odyssey |date=1997 |url=http://s3.amazonaws.com/rdcms-aaa/files/production/public/FileDownloads/pdfs/cmtes/commissions/aec/upload/A_Race_Odyssey.pdf |journal= |access-date=2021-06-09 |archive-date=2021-01-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210110075142/http://s3.amazonaws.com/rdcms-aaa/files/production/public/FileDownloads/pdfs/cmtes/commissions/aec/upload/A_Race_Odyssey.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>，他們既不認同傳統的種族分類方法，亦不同意目前的種族數目，這個概念的某些支持者甚至還提議人種起碼要增加到最少300個<ref name="#2"/>，而目前的基因數據亦無法與演化樹形圖兼容<ref>"Indeed, if a species  has  sufficient  gene  flow,  there  can  be  no  evolutionary tree  of  populations, because there are no population splits...", Templeton, A. (2016). EVOLUTION AND NOTIONS OF HUMAN RACE. In Losos J. & Lenski R. (Eds.), ''How Evolution Shapes Our Lives: Essays on Biology and Society'' (p. 355). Princeton; Oxford: Princeton University Press. {{doi|10.2307/j.ctv7h0s6j.26}}.</ref>。

[[中南大學|中南大學]]分別在2019年和2020年在[[bioRxiv|bioRxiv]]上發表了兩項Y染色體、線粒體和常染色體相關研究，認為東亞人在遺傳特徵上有其明顯的獨特性，並認為其起源與[[非洲起源說|非洲起源說]]有所衝突<ref>{{cite web |author1=Shi Huang et al |title=Ancient Y chromosomes confirm origin of modern human paternal lineages in Asia rather than Africa |url=https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.03.10.986042v1 |website=bioRxiv |access-date=2020-05-12 |archive-date=2020-03-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316075247/https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.03.10.986042v1 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Shi Huang et al |title=Modern human origins: multiregional evolution of autosomes and East Asia origin of Y and mtDNA |url=https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/101410v6.full |website=bioRxiv |access-date=2021-06-15 |archive-date=2021-03-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210306084703/https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/101410v6.full |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 認知科學 ===
西方的種族主義者過去二百多年一直認為東方人智力平庸<ref name="#1"/>。但最近幾十年，有些學者如理查·林恩（Richard Lynn）的研究卻指出東亞族群如華人、朝鮮人、日本人的智商比西方人平均高5分左右，而東南亞人、西伯利亞人、美洲原住民的平均分數亦與西方人無異<ref>{{cite web |author1=Richard Lynn |title=The Intelligence of East Asians: A Thirty-Year Controversy and its Resolution |url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/288737869_The_Intelligence_of_East_Asians_A_Thirty-Year_Controversy_and_its_Resolution |website=Research Gate |accessdate=2006}}</ref>。然而有關此現象原因的研究卻在科學界引發起極大爭議<ref>{{Cite web|last=Quarterly|first=Mankind|title=Mankind Quarterly – About|url=http://mankindquarterly.org/about|access-date=2016-02-04|website=mankindquarterly.org|archive-date=2021-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028101637/http://www.mankindquarterly.org/about|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>Joe L. Kincheloe, et. al, ''Measured Lies: The Bell Curve Examined'', Palgrave Macmillan, 1997, p. 39</ref><ref>Ibrahim G. Aoudé, ''The ethnic studies story: politics and social movements in Hawaiʻi'', University of Hawaii Press, 1999, pg. 111</ref><ref>Kenneth Leech, ''Race'', Church Publishing, Inc., 2005, pg. 14</ref><ref>William H. Tucker, ''The funding of scientific racism: Wickliffe Draper and the Pioneer Fund'', University of Illinois Press, 2002, pg. 2</ref>，如在大學入學試中拉高亞裔考生的分數或提高門檻等逆向種族歧視<ref name="frontline">{{cite web|publisher=[[Public_Broadcasting_System|Public Broadcasting System]]|url=https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/sats/race/summary.html|title=Challenging Race Sensitive Admission Policies|accessdate=2019-11-28|archive-date=2019-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190611221456/https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/sats/race/summary.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。而林恩有關東亞族群平均智商較高的成因所提出的理論<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Kanazawa |first=Satoshi |date=2012-07-01 |title=The evolution of general intelligence |journal=Personality and Individual Differences |language=en |volume=53 |issue=2 |pages=90–93 |doi=10.1016/j.paid.2011.05.015 |issn=0191-8869}}</ref>，亦受到如詹姆斯·弗林（James Flynn）等反對者批评<ref>Flynn, James R. ''Are we getting smarter?: Rising IQ in the twenty-first century''. Cambridge University Press, 2012, pp. 33-35.</ref>。

另有測試指出，東亞種族具有相对其他地區族群的較高平均[[智商|智商]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://hk.news.yahoo.com/%E5%B9%B3%E5%9D%87107-%E6%B8%AF%E4%BA%BAiq%E5%85%A8%E7%90%83%E5%B1%85%E9%A6%96-221111168.html |title=平均107 港人IQ全球居首 |access-date=2017-12-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222052448/https://hk.news.yahoo.com/%E5%B9%B3%E5%9D%87107-%E6%B8%AF%E4%BA%BAiq%E5%85%A8%E7%90%83%E5%B1%85%E9%A6%96-221111168.html |archive-date=2017-12-22 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.setn.com/News.aspx?NewsID=348022 |title=前四名亞洲包辦！台灣人平均智商104 名列全球第3名 |access-date=2018-04-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180419120912/http://www.setn.com/News.aspx?NewsID=348022 |archive-date=2018-04-19 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 唐氏綜合症患者的代名詞 ==
在[[西方國家|西方國家]]，类似于“Albinist”过去曾是用于形容患[[白化病|白化病]]的白人的隐语，「蒙古人种」（Mongoloid）也曾用于指[[唐氏综合症|唐氏综合症]]的患者。這些患者也常被稱作「蒙古白癡」（Mongolian idiocy）和「蒙古低能」（Mongolian imbecility）。之所以會被當作唐氏綜合症患者的代名詞，是因為唐氏綜合症患者總是單眼皮<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.down-syndrome.info/library/periodicals/dsrp/06/1/019/DSRP-06-1-019-EN-GB.htm |author=Ward, Connor O. John Langdon |title=Down the man and the message |year=2006 |publisher=Down-syndrome.info |access-date=2013-12-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060902102759/http://www.down-syndrome.info/library/periodicals/dsrp/06/1/019/DSRP-06-1-019-EN-GB.htm |archive-date=2006-09-02 |url-status=dead }}</ref>。這個贬义在1908年開始出現，直到1950年代仍作為醫學術語使用，至1961年被一班遺傳學專家棄用，並在權威性醫學期刊《刺針》上指出這個用法帶有誤導性的含義，建议改用'''Langdon-Down Anomaly'''、'''Down's Syndrome Anomaly'''或'''Congenital Acromicria'''取代'''Mongolism'''來指代唐氏綜合症<ref>"The importance of this anomaly among Europeans and their descendants is not related to the segregation of genes derived from Asians; its appearance among members of Asian populations suggests such ambiguous designations as 'Mongol Mongoloid'; increasing participation of Chinese and Japanese in investigation of the condition imposes on them the use of an embarrassing term. We urge, therefore, that the expressions which imply a racial aspect of the condition be no longer used. Some of the undersigned are inclined to replace the term Mongolism by such designations as 'Langdon Down Anomaly', or 'Down's Syndrome or Anomaly', or 'Congenital Acromicria'. Several of us believe that this is an appropriate time to introduce the term 'Trisomy 21 Anomaly', which would include cases of simple Trisomy as well as translocations. It is hoped that agreement on a specific phrase will soon crystallise once the term 'Mongolism' has been abandoned."
Allen, G. Benda C.J. et al (1961). Lancet corr. 1, 775.</ref>。在西方世界，相关词句如「Mong」到20世紀後半仍是貶義詞被使用<ref>{{cite news |title=Ricky Gervais, please stop using the word 'mong' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/joepublic/2011/oct/19/ricky-gervais-mong-twitter |publisher=The Guardian |access-date=2012-05-26 |location=London |first=Nicola |last=Clark |date=2011-10-19 |archive-date=2021-12-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221111341/https://www.theguardian.com/society/joepublic/2011/oct/19/ricky-gervais-mong-twitter |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

在21世紀的英語世界，「蒙古人種」（Mongoloid）已被認為是不可接受的詞彙，主要原因是這個詞彙本身帶有冒犯性和誤導性，會令人聯想到這些被稱為是「蒙古人種」（Mongoloid）的族群有唐氏綜合症或智力障礙<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Rodríguez-Hernández|first1=M. Luisa|last2=Montoya|first2=Eladio|date=2011-07-30|title=Fifty years of evolution of the term Down's syndrome|journal=Lancet|volume=378|issue=9789|pages=402|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(11)61212-9|issn=1474-547X|pmid=21803206|s2cid=8541289}}</ref>，故目前已不常用<ref name="Smay and Armelagos">{{cite web |last1=Smay |first1=Diana |last2=Armelagos |first2=George |publisher=Emory University |title=Galileo Wept: A Critical Assessment of the Use of Race in Forensic Anthropology |url=http://www.anthropology.emory.edu/FACULTY/ANTGA/Web%20Site/PDFs/Galileo%20Wept-%20A%20Critical%20Assessment%20of%20the%20Use%20of%20Race%20in%20Forensic%20Anthropology.pdf |access-date=2018-07-20 |archive-date=2018-08-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180818073338/http://www.anthropology.emory.edu/FACULTY/ANTGA/Web%20Site/PDFs/Galileo%20Wept-%20A%20Critical%20Assessment%20of%20the%20Use%20of%20Race%20in%20Forensic%20Anthropology.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Lieberman">{{cite journal |last=Lieberman |first=Leonard |title=Out of Our Skulls: Caucasoid, Mongoloid, Negroid? |doi=10.1111/an.1997.38.9.56 |volume=38 |issue=9 |journal=Anthropology News |page=56 |year=1997}}</ref><ref name="Templeton">{{cite web |last=Templeton |first=Alan R. |work=Washington University |title=Human Races: A Genetic and Evolutionary Perspective |url=http://www.realfuture.org/GIST/Readings/Templeton(1998).pdf |publisher=Realfuture.org |access-date=2018-07-20 |archive-date=2017-08-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170809000654/http://www.realfuture.org/GIST/Readings/Templeton%281998%29.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Keevak">Keevak, Michael. "Becoming Yellow: A Short History of Racial Thinking". Princeton: Princeton University Press, 2011. {{ISBN|978-0-691-14031-5}}.</ref>。而這個術語的轉變是由科學界和醫學界<ref name="Ward1999">{{cite journal|last1=Ward|first1=O Conor|title=John Langdon Down: The Man and the Message|journal=Down Syndrome Research and Practice|url=https://library.down-syndrome.org/en-us/research-practice/06/1/john-langdon-down-man-message/|volume=6|issue=1|year=1999|pages=19–24|issn=0968-7912|doi=10.3104/perspectives.94|doi-access=free|pmid=10890244|access-date=2021-06-09|archive-date=2020-03-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312135934/https://library.down-syndrome.org/en-us/research-practice/06/1/john-langdon-down-man-message/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，以及亞裔人士<ref>{{cite book |author1=Ward, O Conor |title=John Langdon Down: The Man and the Message |date=1999 |url=https://library.down-syndrome.org/en-us/research-practice/06/1/john-langdon-down-man-message/ |access-date=2021-06-09 |archive-date=2020-03-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312135934/https://library.down-syndrome.org/en-us/research-practice/06/1/john-langdon-down-man-message/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，包括蒙古國公民及蒙古族人<ref>{{cite journal|last=Howard-Jones|first=Norman|year=1979|title=On the diagnostic term "Down's disease"|journal=Medical History|volume=23|issue=1|pages=102–04|doi=10.1017/s0025727300051048|pmc=1082401|pmid=153994}}</ref>共同發起的。

